  "market_context": "Strong, steep downtrend in the U.S. Dollar Index after an impulsive move down; price exhibited multiple pullbacks that aligned with Fibonacci retracement levels before resuming downward momentum.",
  "key_observation": "Price consistently pulled back to the 0.382–0.5 Fibonacci retracement zone of prior impulsive moves and then continued downward, confirming the downtrend strength.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Analyst identified a strong, steep downtrend in DXY on the 6-hour chart.",
    "Step 2: Anchored Fibonacci retracement from the swing high (top of impulsive move) to the swing low (bottom of impulsive move).",
    "Step 3: Observed that the first pullback reached the 0.382–0.5 zone and reversed downward.",
    "Step 4: Reapplied Fibonacci from the next swing high to swing low, and again saw price pull back to the same 0.382–0.5 zone before continuing down."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "In strong trends, Fibonacci retracement levels (especially 0.382–0.5) serve as reliable reversal zones for pullbacks; reapplying Fibonacci after each new swing confirms consistent structure.",
